# Core Project Concepts

## Project Structure

```sh
app/
├── components/           # Shared UI components
│   ├── ui/              # Shadcn UI components
│   └── features/        # Feature-specific components
├── lib/                 # Core utilities
│   ├── utils/          # Helper functions
│   ├── hooks/          # Custom hooks
│   └── types/          # Shared types
├── features/           # Feature modules
│   └── [feature]/
│       ├── api/        # Server functions & queries
│       │   ├── queries.ts    # TanStack Query hooks
│       │   └── mutations.ts  # TanStack Mutations
│       ├── components/ # Feature components
│       │   ├── index.ts      # Component exports
│       │   └── [Component]/  # Component files
│       ├── hooks/     # Feature hooks
│       │   └── index.ts      # Hook exports
│       ├── utils/     # Feature utilities
│       └── types/     # Feature-specific types
└── routes/             # Route components
    └── [feature]/      # Feature routes
```

## Technology Stack

### Core Technologies

- React 19 with automatic batching
- TypeScript with strict mode
- TanStack Router for type-safe routing
- TanStack Query for data fetching
- TanStack Start for server functions
- TanStack Form for form handling
- Drizzle ORM for database operations

### UI Layer

- Shadcn UI for components
- Tailwind CSS v4 for styling
- Radix UI for primitives

### Data Layer

- PostgreSQL for database
- Drizzle ORM for queries
- Zod for validation

## Development Standards

### Code Organization

1. Feature-First Organization

   - Group related code by feature
   - Keep feature-specific code isolated
   - Share common code through lib/

2. Type Safety

   - Use TypeScript strict mode
   - Define clear interfaces
   - Validate data at boundaries

3. State Management Hierarchy

   1. URL State (TanStack Router)
   2. Server State (TanStack Query)
   3. Form State (TanStack Form)
   4. Local State (React useState)

4. Code Splitting
   - Split code by routes
   - Lazy load heavy components
   - Optimize bundle size

### Naming Conventions

1. Files and Directories

   - Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
   - Utilities: `camelCase.ts`
   - Server Functions: `$camelCase`
   - Hooks: `use[Name]`
   - Routes: `$paramName.tsx` or `route.tsx`
   - Directories: `kebab-case`

2. Component Props

   ```typescript
   type ComponentProps = {
     /** Description of children prop */
     children: React.ReactNode;
     /** Description of className prop */
     className?: string;
   };
   ```

3. Function Names
   - Actions: `handleClick`, `onSubmit`
   - Queries: `useUserQuery`
   - Mutations: `useCreateUser`
   - Server Functions: `$getUser`

### Best Practices

1. Component Design

   - Single responsibility
   - Composable interfaces
   - Clear prop contracts
   - Consistent patterns

2. Data Flow

   - Unidirectional data flow
   - Predictable state updates
   - Clear data dependencies

3. Error Handling

   - Use error boundaries
   - Handle API errors
   - Validate user input
   - Provide feedback

4. Performance

   - Optimize renders
   - Handle loading states
   - Manage data caching

5. Testing

   - Unit tests with Vitest
   - Component tests with RTL
   - Integration tests for flows
   - E2E tests for critical paths

6. Documentation
   - Use JSDoc for functions
   - Document API endpoints
   - Keep README files updated
   - Include setup instructions

### Standard.js Rules

- Use 2 space indentation
- Use spaces over tabs
- Use single quotes for strings
- Use semicolons
- No unused variables
- Add space after keywords
- Always use === instead of ==
- Space infix operators
- Space after commas
- Keep else on same line
- Use curly braces for multi-line if
- Handle err function parameter
- Use camelCase for variables
- Use PascalCase for components

### Import Organization

```typescript
// 1. React imports
import { useState } from 'react';

// 2. External libraries
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { z } from 'zod';

// 3. Internal absolute imports
import { type User } from '~/types';

// 4. Internal relative imports
import { UserCard } from './UserCard';
```

## Development Workflow

1. Planning

   - Break down requirements
   - Design component structure
   - Plan data flow
   - Consider edge cases

2. Implementation

   - Follow type-safe patterns
   - Write clean, maintainable code
   - Handle errors gracefully
   - Add proper documentation

3. Testing

   - Write unit tests
   - Test edge cases
   - Verify accessibility
   - Check performance

4. Review

   - Code review
   - Self-review checklist
   - Performance audit
   - Accessibility audit

5. Deployment
   - Build optimization
   - Environment checks
   - Monitoring setup
   - Error tracking
